# ── Frontend (Vite exposes only VITE_* vars to the browser) ──────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ── Server-side only (Vercel serverless functions, never sent to browser) ─────
# Required by api/risk/check.ts and api/webhooks/test.ts.
# Get this from Supabase → Project Settings → API → service_role key.
# NEVER commit or expose this value.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# Optional: Vercel also reads SUPABASE_URL as the preferred server-side name.
# Set this alongside VITE_SUPABASE_URL for stricter separation.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

# ── Optional: AI summaries ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When set, risk check responses will use GPT-4o-mini summaries instead of
# the built-in template engine. Falls back gracefully if missing or on error.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ── Stripe billing (api/billing/*) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get these from your Stripe dashboard (https://dashboard.stripe.com).
# Without these vars the Billing tab still renders but Upgrade buttons return 503.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...          # or sk_test_... for testing
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...        # from Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks → endpoint secret
# STRIPE_PRICE_STARTER=price_...         # Monthly Price ID for Starter plan
# STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...             # Monthly Price ID for Pro plan
